"Better World Spirits is driven by the belief that there is a higher purpose for business than profit."






















OUR MISSION






At Better World Spirits, we’re creating delicious, all-naturally crafted hard sodas that support local sustainable agriculture and a healthier world. With an assortment of exciting fresh flavors, Better World Spirits will tap into the new and growing markets of canned cocktails and socially responsible consumerism.

































WHAT IS HARD SODA?




Better World Spirits are specially crafted sodas mixed with vodka and packaged in convenient 12 oz. recyclable cans that can easily be taken to the beach, grabbed at a bar, thrown in an ice bucket at parties, or opened at home. Hard soda makes for a refreshing adult take on a kids beverage.















PENNSYLVANIA PRIDE




Better World Spirits is Pennsylvania-based and proud of it. We want to give back to the state we call home by supporting our communities and neighbors. We want Better World Spirits to distribute within Pennsylvania for now. With Pennsylvania’s population of over 8,843,276 aged 21 and over, and with more than 20,000 establishments with liquor licenses, we believe this focused direction is a responsible, lucrative and achievable goal.













OUR COMPETITIVE EDGE






PROVIDING AN ARTISANAL ALTERNATIVE WITH ENDLESS FLAVOR








Canned cocktails are relatively new to the hard beverage market. Millenials and other hard beverage consumers are limited to malt-based concoctions using same-old, same-old sodas like root beer and ginger beer. Better World Spirits will be a welcome change for Millennials and other adult beverage consumers who are on the lookout for less-sweet, ready-to-drink alternatives with an ever-growing, innovative assortment of flavors that will pique their curiosity and satisfy their adventurous tastes. In 2015, Distilled Spirits Council of the United States reported that discovery and innovation is what drives Millennial consumer purchasing and promotion. They are not OK with simply hard root beer. They also want natural ingredients they can recognize. They demand premium artisanal products and more interesting flavors. Better World Spirits hears them and is happy to provide.
























OUR POTENTIAL FLAVOR COMBINATIONS

















Strawberry Elderflower Cucumber Agave Mint Raspberry BasilBlood Orange Ginger















Blueberry LavenderBlack Cherry Hibiscus Green Apple CinnamonCranberry Ginger Lime















Strawberry LemonPeach BasilGreen Tea GingerJuniper Citrus Cucumber













MIXING BUSINESS WITH PURPOSE






Better World Spirits also differentiates itself from its competitors by believing that businesses can contribute to a better world for our children, grandchildren and future generations while still making a profit. We intend to support local sustainable and urban agriculture by giving to groups such as the Pennsylvania Association for Sustainable Agriculture—the largest statewide, member-based sustainable farming organization in the United States. We also want to make our mission, your mission.











































TRANSPARENT BUSINESS MODEL






Local and national competitors may have corporate and social responsibility departments, but it is often unclear what they do and how it impacts people. Better World Spirits formed as a benefit corporation so we can be held accountable using a transparent business model that requires us by law to prepare and distribute an Annual Benefit Report to investors to share our efforts in creating public benefit throughout the year.






SPECIAL DISTILLERY LICENSE FOR MAXIMUM RETURN






Better World Spirits will hold a “limited distillery” license from the Pennsylvania Liquor Control Board, a special license for those producing less than 100,000 gallons of product a year. Unlike larger distilleries that must go through the state liquor control board to distribute their products, a limited distillery license allows us to self-distribute our products and sell directly to establishments — bars, restaurants, resorts, casinos, clubs, etc. —outside of the confines of the state control system for potentially higher profit margin, quicker product placement and larger sales volume.











OUR MARKETS






CONSCIENTIOUS CONSUMERS






The trend to purchase and promote products with a social purpose in mind has been on the rise for some time. According to the 2012 Edelman Good Purpose Study which researches consumer attitudes towards social purpose:

















