STEADY INDUSTRY GROWTH, ESPECIALLY WITH MILLENNIALS

















According to Gallup, the number of adults in the US who consume alcoholic beverages has remained consistent for the past 50 years at 64% (appx 150 million).




For the last 50 years 64% of Americans consume alcoholic beverages















Chris Fehrnstrom, chief marketing officer for Constellation Brands, reported that there are 62 million Millennials of legal drinking age in the Unites States, and in two years another eight million will turn 21.




62 million Millennials of legal drinking age in the Unites States















Nielsen report found that 73% of women surveyed enjoy flavored alcoholic beverages, with the number increasing to 92% for women between the ages of 21-34.




73% of women surveyed enjoy flavored alcoholic beverages








Beverage Information Group began recording the alcopop (sweet, carbonated, alcoholic beverages) market in 2012, when an explosion of new products flooded the market and alcopops were determined to hold 2.8% market share of total beer consumption. Since then, alcopop consumption has increased to 3.5% of total beer market share in the U.S. and continues to rise. Though 3.5% may not sound like much, in 2011 alone, 36 alcopop brands were introduced, comprising 35.6% of the new beer beverages that year. In 2015, Not Your Father’s Root Beer signed a national distribution deal with Pabst and within 12 months earned $92 million in sales. Industry reports predict that the alcopop market share will continue its upward trend, with sales reaching 148 million cases in 2019 - a 32% increase over five years.











JOIN OUR CAUSE






Better World Spirits is an alternative to traditional “me” centered brands. We want to build a community of investors and consumers who are looking to be a part of something with a higher purpose. Join us in the movement to partner business with communities and convert profits into a means for beneficial change. By investing in Better World Spirits’ equity crowdfunding campaign, you can feel good knowing that our mutual success will actively help to better our world.

















Irregular Use of Proceeds






The issuer may incur other Irregular Uses of Proceeds which may include but are not limited to the following: vendor fees and salaries and/or expenses paid to the Company’s directors or officers or their friends or family, any “Administration Expenses” that are not strictly for administrative purposes, any “Travel and Entertainment” expenses, and any repayment of inter-company debt or back payments; provided however, that the foregoing fees or expenses, as applicable, exceed $10,000.













