Love, Tito's
Spread the Love. Make the World a Better Place.












We believe that we're meant to make the world a better place, and Tito's Handmade Vodka is our medium.

			Love has always been at the heart of this company. Back in 1992, years before he sold his first case, Tito started making vodka to give as gifts. Its popularity quickly spread among his friends and family, and he soon became known as "the vodka guy." When Tito decided to really make a go of it in the spirits business, he started supporting charity events around Austin one bottle at a time, and gave away, by all reasonable standards, a ridiculous amount of vodka. 
			







Spreading Love To
Change the World

Tito asked you to "tell 20 of your closest friends, and we’ll just keep this thing rolling." You did, and every time one of you shared your love for Tito's Handmade Vodka with your friends and family we grew — into new communities, new states, and even new countries. In every new place we were able to reciprocate by pouring that love back into the people and organizations that nurture, support, and empower their local communities and causes.
At some point, after twenty of those friends each told twenty of their friends and so on, it occurred to us that Tito's Handmade Vodka was doing more than just raising spirits. It appeared as though it was our medium to do what we were meant to do — work to make the world a better place.
Last year we were able to use this medium to give to local and national charities supporting disaster relief, the environment, military and veterans, healthcare and medical research, food and beverage industry workers, arts and culture organizations, the LGBTQ community, and the truest form of love on the planet: our pets.
And we're just getting started, y'all.
So, thank you for your unwavering support and generosity. Together we are spreading love to change the world.
Love, Tito's





"Every single person we have worked with at Tito's has embraced our cause and been an absolute pleasure to work with."

David Bales – Chairman, Texans for Cures



"Thank you again for your support, and know that in Massachusetts there is a mom serving your vodka smiling each time she makes a drink, as she is reminded of your support to CORE and to her own family."

Wendy Schryver – beneficiary, Children of Restaurant Employees



"Because of you, we are able to continue to fund our housing program, allowing 40 LGBT youth to receive supportive housing, job training/workforce development, behavioral health care and change their lives for good."

Nate Rhoton – Development Director, One-N-Ten



"The support of Tito's this past year has been invaluable! Just in the last few months, we've been able to be double the number of teachers we serve - encouraging more and more students to embrace sustainability and become leaders for positive change. With the help of generous, community partners such as Tito's, we are able to accelerate our impact and join forces to build a better world."

Gina LaMotte – Execute Director, EcoRise Youth Innovations








Our
Partners

We proudly partner with over 6,000 non-profits.Here are the ones we support through our web store right now.



Emancipet
Making high-quality spay/neuter and veterinary care affordable and accessible to all pet owners.



The Elizabeth Taylor AIDS Foundation
Supporting the organizations delivering direct care and services to people living with HIV and AIDS, often to the most marginalized populations.



American Red Cross
Preventing and alleviating human suffering in the face of emergencies by mobilizing the power of volunteers and the generosity of donors.



Operation Homefront
Assisting military families during difficult financial times by providing food assistance, auto and home repair, vision care, travel and transportation, moving assistance, and rent-free transitional housing for wounded veterans and their families.



Children of Restaurant Employees (CORE)
Supporting the children of food and beverage employees who are navigating life-altering circumstances or conditions.







